The paper investigates the approximation power of random neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) in the analysis of the approximation rate. Additionally, the paper discusses the construction and properties of random neural networks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Systems and Control).
